div.p:
The earthly
Literally “lower” (ներքին). groom becomes happy in watching
i.e. staying up late at the wedding party. Here and throughout this Kc‘urd, the same word is used by the translator to refer to the staying up late of the groomsmen of the earthly groom at the wedding party. It is the same word he uses for the keeping watch of the groomsmen of the heavenly groom: հսկումն. instead of mourning;

listBibl.bibl:
_____, Des heiligen Ephraem des Syrers Carmina Nisibena, 4
                    vols. Corpus Scriptorum Christianorum Orientalium 218–9, 240-241 (Louvain, 1961;
                    1963).
